This paper deals with the use of robotic surgical assistants for precision subtasks such as debridement, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also involves the use of deep neural networks (DNNs) and random forests (RFs) for calibration, which falls under the categories of computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of machine learning algorithms such as DNNs and RFs also suggests the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with the automation of surgical tasks, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
